04:57.969 --> 05:09.906
And Paul's writing to them, and he's giving them this confidence that even in the midst of all this, even in the midst of this, God's working, he's going to work this out for our good.

05:09.986 --> 05:12.990
half of Romans 8, the second half of it is really all about this.

05:13.010 --> 05:15.414
And I'll read some verses around it to get of it some context.

05:15.754 --> 05:23.906
In Romans 8 verses 18 through 22, I consider that our present sufferings are not worth comparing with the glory that will be revealed in us.

05:24.286 --> 05:28.593
For the creation waits in eager expectation for the children of God to be revealed.

05:28.613 --> 05:35.282
For the creation was subjected to frustration not by its own choice, but by the will of the one who subjected it in hope.

05:35.394 --> 05:40.946
that the creation itself will be liberated from its bondage to decay and brought into the freedom

05:40.994 --> 05:42.576
and glory of the children of God.

05:42.936 --> 05:50.723
We know that the whole creation has been groaning as in the pains of childbirth right up to the present time.

05:50.783 --> 05:53.546
