Now he says this, all things together for good.

15:10.306 --> 15:23.987
Now this is the controversial part, because it's like we know that God's working, but then we say for good, people quit on God, and they say like, I don't like the all things.

15:24.007 --> 15:24.948
I don't like the good.

15:25.008 --> 15:26.290
I don't like the good.

15:26.370 --> 15:28.813
And so let me tell you what this verse does not say.

15:28.853 --> 15:36.282
This verse does not say if you love God, no bad things are ever, ever gonna happen.

15:36.302 --> 15:37.924
Doesn't say that, all right?

15:38.645 --> 15:44.171
It doesn't say that whatever happens in your life is good, okay?

15:44.452 --> 15:48.376
It says that he's working it for good, okay?

15:48.637 --> 15:56.306
So there are things that happen to us that are bad things and it's okay to say that's a bad thing.

15:56.770 --> 15:59.614
And you could say that's a bad thing, but he's a good God.

16:00.595 --> 16:00.876
Okay?

16:01.156 --> 16:01.777
It's weird.

16:01.897 --> 16:02.238
It's weird.

16:02.258 --> 16:09.568
I grew up in a church where, you know, like you'd say like, yeah, we're battling, our loved one's battling cancer.

16:09.588 --> 16:11.270
And they're like, praise God for cancer.

16:11.290 --> 16:13.413
I'm like, nope, not gonna praise God for cancer.

16:13.774 --> 16:14.675
Not like in cancer.

16:14.775 --> 16:16.758
Cancer's not a friend in our family.

16:16.798 --> 16:18.961
We'd like to kick cancer out of our family.

16:18.981 --> 16:19.942
They're like, well, praise God.

16:20.202 --> 16:21.925
I'm like, God can work this for good.

16:22.125 --> 16:25.650
I get that, but I am not gonna walk down the street like God cancer.

16:25.762 --> 16:27.624
Hallelujah, you know, I'm not gonna do that, all right?

16:27.905 --> 16:30.268
That's odd in a weird way, how many know what I'm talking about?

16:31.609 --> 16:54.418
It's okay to say, God's working this out, I don't know why, I don't know how, but he's gonna work this for good in my life, because I'm devoted to him, I love him, and I don't know what he's doing, he's working something in me and through me and around me, and I thank God, but that word, I hope, is eradicated out of our family, and I'm praying against that thing,

16:54.562 --> 16:59.067
In the midst of this, I'm gonna say God's working good, all right?

16:59.347 --> 17:04.573
And again, sometimes it's just odd, like the church that I grew up in, and sometimes it's people be the oddest thing.

17:04.873 --> 17:05.834
Praise God, I'm sick.

17:06.375 --> 17:08.076
And then somebody say, no, you're not sick.

17:08.097 --> 17:08.937
You're like, okay, I'm not sick.

17:09.098 --> 17:14.103
You know, and they'd be fighting over words and who's gonna be more positive and who's gonna thank God for everything bad.

17:14.143 --> 17:15.244
And I'm broke, praise God.

17:15.464 --> 17:17.527
I'm like, I don't think it's good, you know?

17:17.547 --> 17:19.849
It's not good, you know?

17:19.869 --> 17:24.434
He's working good, but let's pray for not that.

17:24.706 --> 17:25.066
You know?

17:30.853 --> 17:35.638
This verse doesn't say that if you have enough faith, nothing bad is gonna happen to you.

17:35.658 --> 17:37.761
It doesn't even say that you're gonna understand what he's doing.

17:38.281 --> 17:41.044
It doesn't even say that he's gonna give you an explanation this side of heaven.

17:41.285 --> 17:46.410
There are things that I have put in my life that are in the column of I'll find out in heaven.

17:47.151 --> 17:47.772
I'll find out in heaven.

17:47.892 --> 17:49.674
I don't know all the good.

17:49.994 --> 17:53.298
And anytime something bad happens in our world or in our life,

17:53.378 --> 17:58.206
Even if I don't see something, like it doesn't make sense, all the dots aren't connected.

17:58.927 --> 17:59.968
All the dots aren't connected.

18:00.449 --> 18:02.973
I still just say, okay, what are you doing for the good?

18:03.333 --> 18:04.315
How are you working?

18:04.676 --> 18:05.537
Where are you working?

18:06.038 --> 18:06.979
Will you let me see this?

18:07.159 --> 18:16.754
Even if you don't let me see this, I'll trust you because I know that your word is true, and even though I can't see where it's working good, I'm gonna trust you.

18:17.475 --> 18:21.682
I'm gonna trust you that you are working all things for our good.

18:21.858 --> 18:28.253
It's going to work out in some way for your glory and for your honor, and it's going to be for good.

18:29.015 --> 18:38.077
Now, I want to be clear that the word all things here comes from the word panta, and this word speaks of totality with an emphasis on each individual part.

18:38.458 --> 18:40.242
Everything, no exceptions.

18:40.450 --> 18:42.534
All things work together for good.

18:42.774 --> 18:45.359
All things, they're going to work together for good.

18:45.679 --> 18:51.449
Doesn't mean they're good things, but all things are gonna work together for good for the Christian.

18:51.670 --> 18:54.495
If you're not a Christian, you don't have any claim on this verse.

18:54.535 --> 18:55.476
This is not yours.

18:55.757 --> 19:00.205
But for Christian, those that love God, all things are gonna work together for good.

19:00.545 --> 19:01.447
He's going to do it.

19:01.687 --> 19:05.554
And it's every single thing that is out there.

19:06.274 --> 19:07.576
And he says, they're gonna work together.

19:07.596 --> 19:10.399
And the word that is used there is a word meaning synergy.

19:10.439 --> 19:13.043
We use that a lot in today's day and age, like it's synergy.

19:13.063 --> 19:14.264
We're working together as a synergy.

19:14.484 --> 19:25.478
There's a cooperation and because we're working together and there's like new energy and it's actually us working together and doing these two things together has brought us synergy and it's giving good things from us coming together.

19:25.498 --> 19:33.929
I mean, I'll give you something that apart from each other is poison, but when it's worked together, it's good.

19:34.269 --> 19:34.770
Salt.

19:35.618 --> 19:43.571
Salt is actually amazing when sodium and chlorine get together and make sodium chloride and it flavors our food.

19:43.792 --> 19:48.539
But sodium by itself and chlorine too much, if you happen by themselves, they can kill you.

19:48.920 --> 19:53.147
But when they come together and they're working together, it's good.

19:53.187 --> 19:54.169
How many know what I'm talking about?

19:54.209 --> 19:54.930
Pass the salt.

19:55.970 --> 19:57.952
God is saying, I'm working all things.

19:58.152 --> 19:59.494
All things are working together.

19:59.814 --> 20:01.096
Everything's working together.

20:01.376 --> 20:02.978
God is working things together.

20:02.998 --> 20:05.681
And as he's working them together, we're trusting him.

20:05.921 --> 20:07.162
And we may not understand it.

20:07.202 --> 20:10.646
We may not get a revelation for years and years to come.

20:10.726 --> 20:12.969
We may never get it, but he is working.

20:13.690 --> 20:15.892
And in the Bible, I think about this with Joseph.

20:16.953 --> 20:20.397
If you don't know the story in the Bible, Joseph had all these brothers.

20:20.677 --> 20:23.941
They were jealous of him and they sold him into slavery.

20:23.961 --> 20:25.042
It's found in Genesis.

20:25.378 --> 20:27.401
They sell him into slavery as brothers do.

20:27.422 --> 20:33.191
They're jealous of him because his father has said like, you're my favorite and he gave him a coat of many colors and so they're jealous.

20:33.692 --> 20:35.535
So they sell him into slavery years later.

20:35.596 --> 20:37.218
There's a famine on the land.

20:37.659 --> 20:42.167
Joseph has now risen to the place of right hand of the Pharaoh in Egypt.

20:43.409 --> 20:47.416
And God, there's a famine and so his brothers come looking for food.

20:47.436 --> 20:50.962
They hear that there's food in Egypt and then he sees his brothers.

20:51.266 --> 20:53.551
And that through the whole story, there's this revelation.

20:53.852 --> 21:04.715
And Joseph says this, you intended to harm me, but God intended it for good to accomplish what is now being done, the saving of many lives.

21:05.537 --> 21:06.258
It's amazing.

21:06.690 --> 21:08.833
That's like the end of the story.

21:09.053 --> 21:09.995
We have the start of the story.

21:10.395 --> 21:22.193
Great, he's with his brothers, he's got to code many colors, but it's the in between all these things that are happening, thrown in jail, all these things that are happening, falsely accused, boom, boom, boom, all these things are happening.

21:22.213 --> 21:26.940
But then he comes back over here and he's like, you meant it for harm, but God meant it for good.

21:27.220 --> 21:31.306
God has finally given me a glimpse that it's working together.

21:31.326 --> 21:33.530
I couldn't have seen it along the way.

21:33.610 --> 21:36.434
I never had an idea that it would come out like this.

21:36.514 --> 21:40.061
but it worked together and God got us through this.

21:41.063 --> 21:49.320
Pastor Sam Storm says this, God is able to cause all things people do to us, even the bad things to work together for our good.

21:49.841 --> 21:56.835
That isn't to say that all things are good, but that God can orchestrate the evil into a symphony of glory.

21:57.696 --> 21:58.578
God can do that.

21:59.106 --> 22:13.308
God can do it and you can take all these things and he moves it and he does this and he moves them over there and he gets them there and all of a sudden this happens and that happens and you get glimpses as you walk with God long enough it's like an open ended math problem.

22:13.328 --> 22:17.554
I wasn't very good at math but I do know that like the open end like you have the present and you got

22:17.954 --> 22:20.338
When you solve this one, then this one can be solved.

22:20.358 --> 22:21.299
Then this one can be solved.

22:21.319 --> 22:22.120
Then this one can be solved.

22:22.261 --> 22:23.342
Then this one can be solved.

22:23.482 --> 22:24.524
That's how it's gonna be with God.

22:24.704 --> 22:28.490
And when you get to heaven, if they're not closed out at the end, he's like boom, boom, boom, boom, boom.

22:28.510 --> 22:30.132
And you're gonna be like, I'll make sense.

22:31.234 --> 22:31.895
I'll make sense.

22:32.877 --> 22:35.240
He's working it for our good.

22:35.320 --> 22:36.682
Now, let me get on with that.

22:37.183 --> 22:40.608
Our good and his good don't always align.

22:40.929 --> 22:43.453
We don't understand the good that he's working.

22:43.493 --> 22:44.334
How many know what I'm talking about?

22:44.354 --> 22:47.058
I couldn't help but think of

22:47.298 --> 22:51.905
a movie when I was growing up, Karate Kid with Ralph Machia.

22:51.945 --> 22:54.328
How many like the old, the original Ralph Machia, right?

22:54.348 --> 22:56.712
Yeah, I'm old there, yeah, I remember that.

22:57.072 --> 23:12.956
And I remember us getting frustrated too, like, and then that scene, he's like, oh, you've been doing this, make me wax the car, and paint the fence, and sand the floor, and all this, and I already learned Karate, and then he's like, you know, wax on, and paint the fence, you know, and I was like, that was so cool.

23:12.976 --> 23:17.042
The whole time he's complaining, he doesn't realize,

23:17.122 --> 23:23.272
Somebody smarter than him is working all things for his good and actually getting into the spot that he needs to be in.

23:23.913 --> 23:27.980
And God's working it for our good, but we're complaining so much.

23:28.501 --> 23:29.963
But I've observed this about God.

23:30.324 --> 23:32.768
God is more greater good than now good.

23:33.770 --> 23:37.877
He is now good, but he's more concerned about greater good.

23:38.117 --> 23:41.202
I know, I want to explain that well because

23:41.410 --> 23:45.156
I still believe we live in the favor of God and the blessings of God.

23:45.476 --> 23:53.929
And every time I get something from God or a favor or something breaks my way and God gives me a blessing, I always say, I'm blessed to be a blessing.

23:54.290 --> 23:57.214
And many times I'll say, who am I that I would even get this God?

23:57.234 --> 23:59.318
This is, I wanna be a good steward of this.

23:59.358 --> 24:00.259
I wanna bless you.

24:00.700 --> 24:02.843
How do you want me to live blessed to be a blessing with this?

24:03.063 --> 24:05.006
So I understand that, okay?

24:05.287 --> 24:10.034
But I realize this that God is more concerned with like,

24:10.498 --> 24:13.282
the greater good than are now good.

24:13.923 --> 24:15.505
And that's tough for me to understand.

24:15.565 --> 24:17.088
It's tough for all of us to understand.

24:18.750 --> 24:20.453
He's concerned with our spiritual good.

24:21.474 --> 24:24.699
We think it'd be good if we had all the money we wanted.

24:25.981 --> 24:30.467
And God's like, no, I think it'd be good if you had all the faith I want you to have.

24:31.789 --> 24:32.290
It's different.

24:32.550 --> 24:33.592
It's a different system.

24:34.033 --> 24:37.778
We think that a big 401k would be good

24:37.954 --> 24:41.658
And God says, looking like Jesus is good.

24:42.679 --> 24:48.506
And so where sometimes our good and his good, totally different good, does that make sense?

24:48.846 --> 24:52.270
And so you say, I'm working it out and my good that I have.

24:52.610 --> 24:56.534
It may not make sense, but I am forming you into the image of Jesus.

24:56.815 --> 25:00.058
And as I'm working this, I'm forming you into the image of Jesus.

25:00.078 --> 25:02.781
Remember I talked about my life was like an EKG.

25:03.182 --> 25:05.084
These were moments that I celebrated.

25:05.124 --> 25:07.026
These were moments that I grew.

25:08.738 --> 25:10.860
These are moments that I said, thank you, Jesus.

25:11.240 --> 25:14.023
These were moments that I said, I love you, Jesus.

25:15.504 --> 25:17.166
And things were formed in me.

25:17.947 --> 25:20.509
And things fell away from me that weren't important.

25:21.190 --> 25:23.212
And God changed me more into his image.

25:23.612 --> 25:24.853
And I look back on my life.

25:24.893 --> 25:38.546
I don't know what famous guy said it, but there's a famous guy and he said, like, when you look back on your life, it was those struggles, those tough times that God was actually forming you into his image and you wouldn't trade them for the world.

25:40.162 --> 25:47.011
So he's saying, I'm gonna work that spiritual good for you, and you're gonna be formed into the image of Jesus.

25:48.192 --> 25:57.104
There's an eternal good that lasts forever, that the things that are on this earth don't last, but the things that are for eternity last forever.

25:57.424 --> 26:00.188
And Paul says this in 2 Corinthians 4, 17.

26:00.528 --> 26:08.178
He says, for our light and momentary troubles are achieving for us an eternal glory that far outweighs them all.

26:09.250 --> 26:16.200
And if you're wondering what he's talking about in 2 Corinthians 11, he gives a whole list of things that he's gone through, shipwrecked and being stoned to death and all these different things.

26:16.440 --> 26:20.445
And he's like these light and momentary things, they're working out a far greater glory.

26:20.465 --> 26:23.570
Like it's for eternity, like this God's working out.

26:23.590 --> 26:29.638
He's like, I understand the complexities of God and the light and momentary things that we're going through, God's working out.

26:29.858 --> 26:32.983
And it's for our good and it's for his glory.

26:33.003 --> 26:34.164
And he's always working.

26:34.384 --> 26:38.450
And if we work with him, we can get a glimpse of what he's doing within us.

26:39.490 --> 26:43.095
And I'm praying that this verse will become an anchor verse to you.

26:43.336 --> 26:58.518
The Romans 828 will be that verse when you're going through the struggle, when you're going through the trial, you'll realize like God is with us, God is for us, he's working, he's maneuvering things at a dimension I can't even understand.

26:59.720 --> 27:06.290
I pray that you get a few of these moments in your life where you go through it and you don't know like how does this even make sense, God.

27:06.370 --> 27:10.956
How in the world can this pain or this struggle or what I'm going through make any sense?

27:11.197 --> 27:16.203
And then he shows you, I got you there to get you here to reach this person.

27:16.684 --> 27:22.452
I got you there to go through this so that fell off of you so you could handle this.

27:23.253 --> 27:29.121
Had you been that person over here, that person would not have handled my blessing in that way.

27:29.502 --> 27:35.730
I did this to get you, I pray that he gives you a few of those moments that you understand.

27:36.674 --> 27:38.536
I pray that He connects the dots.

27:38.977 --> 27:50.211
And I'll never forget years ago, years, years ago, somebody quit our church and devastated Beck and I said, we were horrible pastors, horrible people.

27:50.231 --> 27:51.132
The church was very small.

27:51.452 --> 27:52.453
They were dear friends of ours.

27:52.473 --> 27:55.657
They said, you're terrible pastors, you're terrible people, you're horrible people.

27:56.318 --> 27:59.442
And it devastated us for years.

27:59.522 --> 28:06.532
We clung to God, we prayed, we looked inside, we did whatever, and we just lived with this mystery of like, what happened?

28:06.773 --> 28:11.700
They actually moved out of town, and we never even said goodbye, and we're like living with this pain for years.

28:12.581 --> 28:17.648
Until one day she knocked at the door, we hadn't seen her in years, and she said, hey, I'm here.

28:17.969 --> 28:19.651
I just wanted to tell you that you didn't do anything wrong.

28:19.992 --> 28:24.579
My husband and I weren't a bad time there, and you didn't do anything wrong.

28:25.240 --> 28:26.962
And I'm sorry, it was all on us.

28:27.170 --> 28:27.731
And we're sorry.

28:27.952 --> 28:29.755
And when she left that night, we prayed for her.

28:29.996 --> 28:35.287
And then Beck and I broke down in our lobby of our home, in our foyer area, and we just started bawling.

28:36.429 --> 28:40.097
And we're like, God, thanks for connecting the dots.

28:40.117 --> 28:40.999
That sure hurt.

28:41.781 --> 28:43.484
But we sure did a lot of soul searching.

28:43.524 --> 28:44.306
We did a lot of

28:44.450 --> 28:46.213
diving deep into you.

28:46.273 --> 28:48.696
We learned that you were the one that was gonna affirm us.

28:49.097 --> 28:50.419
You were the one that called us.

28:50.819 --> 28:52.963
You were the one that was validating our ministry.

28:53.243 --> 28:57.069
If we had to look at people, we could always have someone attack us and criticize us.

28:57.369 --> 28:59.392
And I look at like what God did in that.

28:59.612 --> 29:00.834
And he finally connected that.

29:00.874 --> 29:01.856
He doesn't always do that.

29:01.936 --> 29:06.022
You don't always get that knock on the door that says, I'm gonna wrap this up.

29:06.222 --> 29:08.345
God was doing something through this mess.

29:08.365 --> 29:09.147
That wasn't fun.

29:09.427 --> 29:10.489
That was not enjoyable.

29:10.769 --> 29:11.570
That was painful.

29:11.871 --> 29:14.194
But God shaped us through that struggle.

29:14.434 --> 29:15.795
and he got us through to the other side.

29:17.357 --> 29:19.979
I'm telling you that God is at work.

29:19.999 --> 29:23.062
He's looking and doing things that you can't even comprehend.

29:23.943 --> 29:25.425
And when we say God, I'll trust you.

29:25.705 --> 29:26.926
I'll stay with you no matter what.

29:27.326 --> 29:28.788
The devil's gonna throw things at me.

29:28.808 --> 29:30.590
There's gonna be, but you're gonna reverse it.

29:30.610 --> 29:31.611
You're gonna switch it around.

29:31.891 --> 29:32.892
You're gonna work it for good.

29:32.932 --> 29:35.614
And I'm gonna stay in love with you and trust you.

29:36.015 --> 29:39.618
Even if you don't reveal it, I wanna be formed into your image and trust you.

29:39.658 --> 29:40.739
I'm never walking out.

29:41.040 --> 29:42.141
I'm never walking away.

29:42.401 --> 29:43.602
Somebody needs to hear that.

29:44.194 --> 29:50.602
Somebody needs to hear that in a church like ours that has been growing as rapidly and as fast as we have, and people saying yes to Jesus.

29:50.962 --> 29:54.146
When you face a struggle, when you face a trial, you think you're a failure.

29:54.166 --> 29:57.210
When you face a struggle, when you face a trial, you think, well, God doesn't care.

29:57.230 --> 29:58.252
No, he cares.

29:59.413 --> 30:01.175
He's been watching all along.

30:01.195 --> 30:02.577
You've been working behind the scenes.

30:02.897 --> 30:06.642
He's working a far greater good than you can ever imagine, and we know

30:07.746 --> 30:14.534
That all things work together for good, that God causes all things to work together for good to those who love God and are called according to His purpose.

30:15.035 --> 30:15.575
We know that.

30:16.256 --> 30:16.937
We know that.

30:17.458 --> 30:22.463
And we need to grab hold of that one and grab it like an anchor, like our life depended on it because it does.

30:23.805 --> 30:25.327
I want to pray this over you right now.

30:25.507 --> 30:27.509
Could you bow your heads and close your eyes here and all the campuses?

30:29.252 --> 30:30.393
I just especially feel this.

30:30.733 --> 30:34.738
If you've been walking with God for five years or less, five years or less,

30:35.618 --> 30:38.542
With every head bowed and every eye closed, you've been walking with God for five years or less.

30:38.562 --> 30:39.323
Could you just raise your hand?

30:39.343 --> 30:41.406
I just want to pray over you right now here in all of our campuses.

30:41.446 --> 30:41.947
Yup.

30:41.967 --> 30:43.789
Hands going up in this room and I'm sure in all the room.

30:44.370 --> 30:45.211
Five years or less.

30:46.152 --> 30:50.538
Lord, I just pray right now for those that have been living a shorter time with you.

30:51.179 --> 30:52.000
Just a shorter time.

30:53.082 --> 30:57.969
They need to know that you're going to be with them in the trial, in the struggle, in the storms, in the things that are facing.

30:57.989 --> 31:01.874
They need to know that this verse is an anchor verse that they can grab hold of.

31:03.106 --> 31:10.098
They're gonna grab hold of it and hold on with all their realizing that you are causing these things to work together for good.

31:11.330 --> 31:17.397
God, I pray that their faith would be strong enough in the storms that they'd face, in the trials that they'd face, and they'd grab hold of it.

31:17.417 --> 31:23.463
I pray that they'd find a brother, a sister in Christ that would encourage them and say, I got through mine, you could get through yours.

31:23.743 --> 31:40.882
I pray that they'd be encouraged by people that have had longevity with you and have lived a faith with you for years and years and years, but God, I pray especially for those young in their faith, let them grab hold of this anchor verse and let it get them through the times where they don't understand what's going on.

31:41.122 --> 31:41.985
You're faithful.

31:42.446 --> 31:43.269
You're faithful.

31:43.309 --> 31:44.593
You haven't given up on them.

31:44.975 --> 31:47.804
And anything they go through doesn't mean they're a failure.

31:48.868 --> 31:50.834
It means that you're working behind the scenes.

31:51.074 --> 31:55.779
So God, we pray for young believers right now in Jesus' name that they would have that faith.

31:55.799 --> 32:04.728
And God, I pray for those that are seasoned, God, I pray that they'd be able to share the testimony that God was faithful to me for year after year after year.

32:04.968 --> 32:07.952
He's been able to get me through a time and time again.

32:08.252 --> 32:09.053
I've trusted him.

32:09.273 --> 32:10.474
I've never walked away.

32:11.195 --> 32:18.002
I don't understand it all, but I do believe this anchor verse that he is working all things out for good.

32:18.466 --> 32:19.188
I believe that.

32:19.268 --> 32:25.642
So God, I pray that you'd encourage the veteran mature Christians to be able to encourage people in this way.

32:26.684 --> 32:27.365
Thank you, God.

32:27.967 --> 32:35.924
Thank you, God, for these anchor verses that we hold onto in Jesus' name we pray, amen and amen.

